complaint_what_happened:
b'I, Carlos Deangelo Prunty, Trustee of the XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, file this complaint against Rocket Mortgage, LLC (f/k/a Quicken Loans, LLC).

This matter is already on record with the Federal Trade Commission under Filing Number XXXX  Indiana Attorney General filing XXXX XXXX XXXX  and United States department of the Treasury Criminal investigation Division expanding this record to ensure all agencies are notified of Rocket Mortgages unlawful conduct.

Rocket Mortgage has engaged in:

- Fraudulent lien practices and misrepresentation of lien priority against trust-owned property;
- Unlawful securitization and sale of my mortgage into investment trusts without disclosure, assignment, or consent, in violation of TILA and RESPA;
- Conversion of my credit signature into securities identified by CUSIP, generating undisclosed profits, while continuing to demand fiat payments;
- Dishonor of private settlement instruments, including Bill of Exchange, Conditional Acceptance for Value, and Notice of Tender, leaving all notices unrebutted in default;
- Unjust enrichment through charge-offs, insurance policies, and securitization proceeds, all concealed from the borrower/trustee.

Supporting evidence includes certified mail notices establishing administrative default and dishonor:

- Bill of Exchange / Affidavit of Tender  XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXXn
These notices remain unrebutted, constituting legal default under UCC Articles 3 & 9 and establishing a perfected trust claim.

I request:

1. Recognition and enforcement of my trusts beneficial and equitable title;
2. Immediate investigation and correction of Rocket Mortgages fraudulent lien filing;
3. A full securitization and accounting of the mortgage (including CUSIP and proceeds);
4. Injunction against further foreclosure, collection, or lien enforcement until compliance is achieved;
5. Enforcement action under FTC Act  5, TILA, RESPA, UCC, and RICO statutes as appropriate.

All supporting evidence and certified records are available upon request.'

Mortgage company offered no options for help. Requested forms for assistance were completed but denied. 
Both my husband and I are experiencing severe medical issues and no consideration was given. 
Feel like customer service offered no options Upon reading our closing documents it was going to cost us {$270000.00} for a mobile home we purchased for {$95000.00}
